snippet.title: Johnny Depp vs Amber Heard. Live. Trial Coverage
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp is scheduled to take the stand today, to detail the abuse he suffered at the hands of Amber Heard. We will hear how he was shouted at, belittled, taken advantage of, attacked, slapped many many times, had his withdrawal medication hidden from him, was falsely accused of being the instigator of these arguments, would get black eyes and scratches along with having his finger cut off and nearly dying.

We have already heard evidence from their doctor, nurse and other medical professionals that Amber was the volatile one, the one who instigated these fights, who was never seen with any injuries what so ever. We have heard testimony from others that they also never saw injuries to Heard. 

Later this week we will have further testimony and video footage that will prove, beyond any shadow of a doubt, that the incident at the apartment that effectively ended their relationship, was a complete hoax, staged to frame Johnny. 

Amber has already been accused by many on the stand, of being calculated and to being a strategist. She was always thinking 4 moves ahead, planning the hoax from the start. The evidence will show this. 

If you have never seen the film, Gone Girl, go watch it now. You will get the idea.

snippet.title: Isaac Baruch Is Seriously Confused. What Is Amber Heard's Amica Cream? Lawyer Doesn't Even Know.
snippet.description:
Arnica cream is a first aid application, effective for all types of bruises resulting from injuries, knocks and falls. It contains arnica prepared from the alpine plant Arnica montana - a topical herbal remedy traditionally used in the symptomatic treatment of bruises. It is supposed to help heal bruises faster, certainly not hide them or conceal them. And it's Arnica cream, not Amica.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp vs Amber Heard LIVE Week 2 day 1
snippet.description:
Were back for week 2 and we will be here the entire time offering commentary and showing you the footage from inside the courtroom. We got this.

Live coverage is back as we watch the defamation trial that is taking place in Virginia US. The case is being fought out between 2 of Hollywood's celebrities, not withstanding the superstar of this trial Johnny Depp.

Depp is suing his ex wife Amber Heard for 50mil dollars, and Amber is counter suing for 100mil dollars. Some notable names who will be testifying include Walter Hamada the President of Warner Bros and Elon Musk to name just a couple.

As this trial gets underway for week 2, we can only imagine this is only going to get more intense as the weeks go by. Our live coverage here will help keep you entertained.

snippet.title: Debunking Flat Earth. Brains Logic Fails Again
snippet.description:

snippet.title: Amber Heard & Johnny Depp. Summary Judgement Motion - Stevie J Raw
snippet.description:
In April this year, perhaps the most anticipated court case will finally get heard, with a jury this time, to decide who has been telling the truth and consequently who has been telling some lies. 

I have been following this case for almost a year now and it has become a guilty pleasure of mine, following the clues, the evidence and even the skulduggery. I of course have my very strong opinion of this, having been very objective in the way I looked at everything, so I feel I have listened to both arguments very very thoroughly. This is not an on the whim discussion.

I may be quite biased in my opinions, but again, this is after I did all my own research on this. It is also a subject I am quite passionate about too. Amber Heard Vs Johnny Depp trial is like watching a mini series play out in real time, fascinating.

Link to Stevies channel here https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCAk03rcNVtLK1_LlgRTOh2w

I suspect once the jury have had their say, and I do trust that those people will do the right thing, that there is no doubt in my mind that the ramifications of this has the potential to give a huge shake up to the me-too movement, for what I believe will be for the better.

#JusticeForJohnnyDepp #JohnnyDepp #DeppHeard
